(How it works) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 11 Tf
72 340 Td
(" Auto Renewal triggers when Auto Renewal is enabled AND Next Renewal equals today \(UTC) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 11 Tf
54 326 Td
(date\).) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 11 Tf
72 312 Td
(" When triggered, Trackla renews the subscription by setting Start Date to today and) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 11 Tf
54 298 Td
(advancing Next Renewal based on Billing Cycle.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 11 Tf
72 284 Td
(" A history entry is created with Changed By = System \(Auto-Renewal\).) Tj
ET
BT
/F2 12 Tf
54 270 Td
(How to test \(recommended\)) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 11 Tf
54 254 Td
(1\) Pick a subscription and set Auto Renewal = ON.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 11 Tf
54 240 Td
(2\) Set Next Renewal to today in YYYY-MM-DD format \(example: 2026-05-20\).) Tj
ET
BT
/F2 12 Tf
54 226 Td
(3\) Ensure Status is Active.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 11 Tf
54 210 Td
(4\) Restart the backend once OR wait for the midnight \(IST\) scheduled job.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 11 Tf
54 196 Td
(5\) Verify Start Date updated to today and Next Renewal moved forward correctly.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 11 Tf
54 182 Td
(6\) Check Subscription History for an Auto Renewed entry and date range change.) Tj
ET
BT
/F2 12 Tf
54 168 Td
(Note) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 11 Tf
72 152 Td
(" If Next Renewal is not a valid date, auto renewal will not trigger.) Tj
